  "A scientist uses the formula d = rt to calculate distance. If a car travels 240 miles in 4 hours, what is the rate? Solve the formula for r first.": "",
  "r = 60 mph": "",
  "r = 236 mph": "",
  "r = 960 mph": "",
  "r = 244 mph": "",
  "Rearrange d = rt to r = d/t. Then r = 240/4 = 60 mph.": "",
  "An engineer uses V = lwh to find the volume of a rectangular tank. If V = 600 cubic feet, l = 10 ft, and w = 5 ft, solve for h.": "",
  "h = 120 ft": "",
  "h = 585 ft": "",
  "h = 30000 ft": "",
  "h = 12 ft": "",
  "Rearrange: h = V/(lw) = 600/(10 * 5) = 600/50 = 12 ft.": "",
  "A nurse uses the formula F = (9/5)C + 32 to convert a patient's temperature. If the patient's temperature is 104 degrees F, solve for C.": "",
  "C = 219.2": "",
  "C = 40": "",
  "C = 72": "",
  "C = 57.8": "",
  "C = 5(F - 32)/9 = 5(104 - 32)/9 = 5(72)/9 = 360/9 = 40 degrees C.": "",
